In re HOTCHKISS. (Supreme Court, Appellate Division, First Department. June 3, 1910.) Appeal from Special Term, New York County. Application by William H. Hotchkiss, as Superintendent of Insurance. On appeal from an order. Dismissed.

Argued before INGRAHAM, P. J., and McLAUGHLIN, CLARKE, SCOTT, and DOWLING, JJ.

H. Jones, for appellant. A. H. Stephens, for respondent. PER CURIAM.

Appeal dismissed, with $10 costs and disbursements, for the reasons stated in appeal No. 2 in this proceeding (decided herewith) 123 N. Y. Supp. 511.
